==Mixed==
===Mixed Relay (4 × 6 km)===
This event was first held in 2005, at the [[Biathlon World Cup]] finals in [[Khanty-Mansiysk]]. In 2005 the women biathletes did the first two legs, and the men did the following two, while in 2006 the sequence was woman–man–woman–man. At the [[Biathlon World Championships 2007]] in [[Rasen-Antholz|Antholz]], the sequence was women–women–man–man. The ski legs of 6&nbsp;km each (in 2007–19 men ski legs: 7.5&nbsp;km). From 2007 only one team per nation is allowed to compete.

